Some of these countries are more vulnerable to the impact of climate change have indicated that they would continue to put pressure on obtaining a legally binding treaty in Copenhagen, although most of the main participants say that negotiations will lead to a minimum political agreement.
The Alliance of Small Island States, which brings together 43 members, drafted a 24-page treaty proposal, early Friday morning.
